## Plan Summary

Here's what I found and what needs to change — only **2 files** require edits:

---

### Codebase snapshot
- **`src/data.ts`** — 15 hardcoded `User` objects (the full dataset)
- **`src/types.ts`** — `User` interface only
- **`src/routes.ts`** — `GET /users` currently does `res.json(users)` (no pagination)
- **`tests/routes.test.ts`** — **already has all 4 pagination tests written**, just waiting for the implementation

---

### What changes

**`src/types.ts`** — Add two new interfaces:
```typescript
export interface Pagination {
  page: number; limit: number; total: number; totalPages: number;
}
export interface PaginatedResponse<T> {
  data: T[];
  pagination: Pagination;
}
```

**`src/routes.ts`** — Replace the `GET /users` handler body:
```typescript
const page  = Math.max(1, parseInt(req.query.page  as string, 10) || 1);
const limit = Math.max(1, parseInt(req.query.limit as string, 10) || 10);
const total      = users.length;          // 15
const totalPages = Math.ceil(total / limit);
const start      = (page - 1) * limit;
const data       = users.slice(start, start + limit); // [] when out-of-range
res.json({ data, pagination: { page, limit, total, totalPages } });
```

The `GET /users/:id` handler is **untouched**.

---

### Why this works
| Test case | Result |
|---|---|
| Default (`GET /users`) | page=1, limit=10 → 10 users, totalPages=2 |
| Page 2 (`?page=2&limit=10`) | users 11–15 → 5 items |
| Custom limit (`?limit=5`) | 5 items, totalPages=3 |
| Out-of-range (`?page=100`) | `start=990 >= 15` → `slice()` returns `[]`, status 200 |

**Verification:** `npm test` — all 6 tests pass.
